Which genres are most popular from year to year?¶

In [32]:
# spliting genres and put them in a dataframe
df_geners = df.genres.str.split('|',expand=True)
In [33]:
# gitting the count of each gener type
a = df_geners[0].value_counts()
for i in range(1,5):
    b = df_geners[i].value_counts()
    a = a.add(b, fill_value=0)    
    
# visualizing the count of each gener
a.plot(kind = 'bar')
plt.title('count of each geners')
plt.xlabel("movie type", size=10)
plt.ylabel("number of movies", size=10);

so we got that, Drama is the most one.

which actor more frequent?¶

# spliting cast and put them in a dataframe

Conclusions¶

In this project we analyesd TMDB Movies. First thing we did cleaning our data to be able to work with. Then we exlore some data that can help us to answer some questions that help us to understand this data. last thing we did some data analsys for top 500 movies sorted by average rate and got some good results to explore.

The best movie is The Story of Film: An Odyssey with vote average 9.2.

Avatar is the movie that has highest revenues.

There is no correlation between budget and vote averaged.

The most popular five geners from year to year is drama , comedy thriller, action and romance.

Robert De Niro, Samuel L. Jackson, Bruce Willis, Nicolas Cage and Michael Caine are most freqent actors in the movies.

Then we rearange the data by vote average then take the first 500 and name it as a top 500 movies and we made some data analysis and we got some info.

to make a good movie you should put a budget not less than 17.94 million dollar and the expicted revenue is 97.18 million dollar

Martin Scorsese, Quentin Tarantino, Steven Spielberg, Christopher Nolan and Stanley Kubrick those pepole are genuses they are the best movies directors

The budget status is increaces over the release years.

The Vote average count is increaces over the release years.
